  "metadata": {
    "title": "Roasted kohlrabi with tomato, hazelnuts and tarragon gremolata",
    "description": "‘What is that space alien?’ said someone somewhere, when met with the odd-looking kohlrabi with its long, thin stems sprouting from its globe-shaped base. In contrast to its ‘out-there’ appearance, it is quite a mild-flavoured vegetable and loves bold, rich flavours both in its raw and cooked forms. Feel free to play around with the flavours here, using whatever seeds (cumin or fennel!) and whatever soft herbs (chives or coriander!) you might have on hand. Keep this vegan by swapping out the butter for a generous glug of olive oil instead, and leaving out the cream.",
    "servings": 4,
    "difficulty": "medium",
    "totalTime": "45min",
    "image": "roasted-kohlrabi-with-tomato-hazelnuts-and-tarragon-gremolata.jpg",
