      "title": "Roasted kohlrabi with tomato, hazelnuts and tarragon gremolata",
      "steps": [
        {
          "id": "step1",
          "action": "Preheat the oven to 220°C fan.",
          "tools": [
            "oven"
          ],
          "output": {
            "state": "preparation",
            "description": "Oven preheated."
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "step2",
          "action": "Put the butter, oil, kohlrabi, caraway, tomato paste, tomatoes, sugar, 90ml of water, 1½ teaspoons of salt and a good grind of pepper into a large, 34cm x 26cm roasting tin. Toss everything together and roast for 45 minutes, stirring about four times throughout, until softened, browned in places and the tomatoes have completely broken down. Remove from the oven and add the lemon juice.",
